            PhD Candidate | Geospatial Scientist | Data
            Storyteller
            Welcome to my personal website! I am a PhD candidate in
            sociology at Stanford and will be defending my dissertation
            in August. My research relies upon big spatial data and
            addresses geographic problems such as site selection,
            resource allocation, and geodemographic classification.
            Browse the pages and links on my website to learn more about
            my interests, prior work experience, skills, and
            projects.
